title: For Sale:  Anderson AR15 w/Green Mountain 1:7 Barrel and 4-14x44 PA FFP Scope
postcontent: I am doing some cleaning and consolidating of firearms and ammo in anticipation of an upcoming move, and have decided to sell this rifle. It has right at 225 rounds through it, with 20 of those being LC XM193 55gr FMJ for break-in and 200 being 69gr PPU BTHP match. No steel case has ever been shot. I hand built this rifle myself late last year but just don't shoot it enough to justify keeping it when I shoot my other ARs more. With quality 69gr and 75gr Ammo, it shoots 0.7 MOA and shot sub-half MOA with 5 handloads I tried using 75gr Hornady BTHP and Varget that shoots well in my other rifles. Below are the build specs on the rifle and scope:Anderson A3 Upper + Anderson Upper Build KitAnderson Lower + PSA MOE Lower Parts KitMidwest Industries Gen2 SS RailAnderson M16 Full Auto BCGAnderson CHAnderson Mil-Spec Buffer Tube AssemblyMagpul MOE Carbine StockYHM Low Profile Gas BlockGreen Mountain 16" Fluted 1:7 GM-M6 BarrelA2 Flash HiderPrimary Arms 4-14x44 FFP MIL/MIL ScopePrimary Arms Deluxe Extended 30mm Scope MountI have built over a dozen AR15s for myself and close friends over the years and always build them correctly following all torque specs. I also properly lapped the upper receiver for better barrel alignment and increased accuracy (I do this on all ARs I build). The gun is definitely a good shooting rifle that doesn't break the bank (intended goal of the build). I will sell the gun, scope, and mount for $900, or I will separate the gun and scope/mount for $725 and $250 respectively. I am not interested in any trades. Please be an Alabama resident with a valid drivers license and I would prefer you have a valid Alabama CCP as well. I work in Huntsville near the Gate 9/Research Park area and live in the Grant area, so I am willing to meet in those locations or anywhere in between. Thank you for looking and I look forward to supplying someone with a quality rifle setup who can use it more than I currently am. -Mike
